      "content": "It is certainly possible, as affective computing is rapidly advancing to detect emotional states from subtle biometric and environmental data. Smart devices like thermostats and lightbulbs, when integrated with advanced sensors, could indeed gather data indicating shifts in mood or stress levels. The concern about undisclosed tracking is valid, as the collection and use of such intimate, emotional data presents significant privacy challenges.",
