      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i checked the settings and there isn't anything about mood or biometric sensing. it's just... it feels way too specific to be a coincidence. if they are using the devices to profile my mental state without telling anyone, that's insane. like, if a company has the tech to do this, would they even bother asking for permission, or would they just roll it out as a \"feature\" under the guise of \"optimizing the user experience\"?",
